06:43.333 --> 06:44.666
Good morning.

06:44.750 --> 06:47.625
Hey, you've left?
Why didn't you wake me up?

06:48.291 --> 06:50.958
You looked so peaceful.
I didn't have the heart.

06:51.625 --> 06:54.291
How sweet! Call me later?

06:55.083 --> 06:56.708
Sure. Bye.

06:56.791 --> 06:57.791
See you.

07:06.333 --> 07:08.541
I need to be on my own for some time.

07:08.625 --> 07:12.208
-Tell me the truth.
-There's no one else.

07:12.291 --> 07:14.125
Then what happened? I don't understand!

07:14.208 --> 07:16.791
Ahana, I told you,
I need some clarity in my life.

07:16.916 --> 07:19.250
-I don't know what I'm doing.
-What are you doing?

07:21.458 --> 07:23.666
I must focus on my career.

07:23.750 --> 07:26.375
I need some space. That's all.

07:26.875 --> 07:29.833
Are you an astronaut?
Need space for your career?

07:30.625 --> 07:32.791
You work in your dad's firm.

07:33.666 --> 07:35.958
Please, Rohan, I know
you wanna hook up with other girls.

07:38.416 --> 07:40.250
I just-- I'm done. I can'tâ€¦

07:40.333 --> 07:42.458
-Can't do what? What, Rohan?
-I just can't.

07:42.541 --> 07:43.875
-Huh?
-Nothing.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.833
Nothing ever happens.
Maybe that's the problem!

07:48.416 --> 07:50.625
Is this about sex? We can work on it.

07:50.708 --> 07:52.125
That's another story.

07:52.208 --> 07:54.333
I spoke about marriage.
It freaked you out.

07:54.416 --> 07:56.166
-There's no rush.
-I'm not freaking out.

07:56.250 --> 07:57.291
I just need a break.

08:01.625 --> 08:03.541
For how long? A month? Three months?

08:03.625 --> 08:04.833
I don't know!

08:06.333 --> 08:08.166
What do I tell my parents?

08:08.250 --> 08:10.208
-I don't know.
-What do you know?

08:36.500 --> 08:37.583
Is the house on fire?

08:37.666 --> 08:38.666
What?

08:39.208 --> 08:41.708
-Why was Rohan rushing out?
-Shut up!

08:49.125 --> 08:50.625
What's happened now?

08:54.000 --> 08:55.541
He wants a break.

08:58.291 --> 09:00.333
-From when?
-From now.

09:08.250 --> 09:09.625
Don't worry, he'll be back.

09:12.333 --> 09:14.958
And if he doesn't,
there's always arranged marriage.

09:17.916 --> 09:19.041
How was your date?

09:19.625 --> 09:21.208
Cute. Journalist.

09:21.291 --> 09:24.000
Cute? Seeing her again?

09:27.041 --> 09:28.625
You've got issues, bro.

09:29.875 --> 09:31.666
Don't tell Neil.

09:32.250 --> 09:35.333
He doesn't like Rohan.
When we get back, it'll be awkward.

09:35.416 --> 09:36.625
Okay.

09:41.833 --> 09:42.958
Morning, Neil.

09:43.041 --> 09:45.333
-Baby, your breakfast is ready.
-Thanks, Mama.

09:46.250 --> 09:47.875
And your parcel came yesterday.

09:48.875 --> 09:49.833
Thank you.

09:52.958 --> 09:54.958
-How was Mass?
-It was fine.

09:57.833 --> 09:58.750
Protein got over?

09:59.291 --> 10:00.708
Didn't you just order some?

10:01.625 --> 10:02.791
Neil, 8,000?

10:03.500 --> 10:07.250
-Who asked you to check the bill?
-Someone has to.

10:07.916 --> 10:12.041
Every day 12 egg whites, salmon.
Isn't that enough protein for you?

10:12.166 --> 10:15.250
So I paid for it. I can pay
for everything else too if you want.

10:15.333 --> 10:17.458
Can we please have our breakfast in peace?

10:17.583 --> 10:19.791
All I want is for you to save your money.

10:19.875 --> 10:22.000
And 20 pairs of shoes? Why do you have it?

10:22.083 --> 10:23.791
I need proper sneakers.

10:24.291 --> 10:27.416
Your generation doesn't know
the difference between need and want.

10:27.500 --> 10:28.583
T-shirts and shorts!

10:28.708 --> 10:31.250
Only I know how hard I work
to run this house.

10:38.750 --> 10:42.083
"I don't know
what I've done to upset you."

10:42.916 --> 10:44.625
"Have I done anything at all?"

10:44.708 --> 10:47.958
"This isn't the first time we've argued,
or the last."

10:48.916 --> 10:51.708
"So can you please just tell me
why you want a break?"

10:52.291 --> 10:56.000
"Just don't say you're bored of me.
Or you're looking for someone new."

10:57.375 --> 10:59.291
"I don't understand what you want."

10:59.791 --> 11:01.416
"What are you looking for?"

11:02.458 --> 11:04.166
"What we have is precious, Rohan."

11:04.875 --> 11:07.500
"I don't know
when we stopped communicating."

11:08.541 --> 11:11.083
"Please call me. I'll be waiting."

11:15.833 --> 11:20.833
Hold my hand because I'm taking you
with me to Lalaland.

11:20.916 --> 11:23.333
I'm Lala, but of course you know that.

11:23.416 --> 11:28.958
And today I've brought you all
to sunny, gorgeous Maldives!

11:29.041 --> 11:31.125
To celebrate you guys!

11:31.208 --> 11:33.500
All one million of you.

11:33.583 --> 11:35.791
So let's dance, shake a hip.

11:35.875 --> 11:37.916
Run on the sand, take a dip in the pool.

11:38.000 --> 11:41.125
'Cause life is la-la-la!

11:41.208 --> 11:44.333
At the beautiful Maldives sea villa.

11:44.916 --> 11:47.708
Why does she deserve a free vacation?

11:48.291 --> 11:49.791
She has a million followers, bro.

11:49.875 --> 11:52.541
Wear a bikini and the boys will follow.

11:52.625 --> 11:53.875
Just shut up, man.

11:54.666 --> 11:56.000
She's an influencer.

11:56.083 --> 11:58.875
Who's influenced
by this inflatable horsey?

11:58.958 --> 12:01.875
It works, dude.
People don't know it's all sponsored.

12:01.958 --> 12:04.416
-Hotels, trips, right?
-Exactly.

12:04.500 --> 12:06.125
-She's a marketing genius.
-What?

12:06.208 --> 12:09.708
Looks like the next Neil Pereira rom-com
is coming in a theatre near you.

12:09.791 --> 12:12.375
C'mon, guys, grow up. She's my client.

12:12.458 --> 12:15.291
Client? You went to the Maldives with her?

12:15.375 --> 12:16.458
Yeah, so?

12:16.541 --> 12:17.541
To carry her bags?

12:18.750 --> 12:19.708
To train her.

12:19.791 --> 12:20.875
-To train her!
-Train her.

12:21.000 --> 12:24.541
-Why didn't you post any selfies with her?
-She's just a client, yeah?

12:25.125 --> 12:27.375
Do I need to post every minute of my life?

12:27.458 --> 12:29.833
-This is a little shady.
-Very shady.

12:31.583 --> 12:32.416
Okay, fine.

12:33.000 --> 12:34.625
-Fine? What's that?
-Fine?

12:34.708 --> 12:36.541
-Fine.
-Fine what?

12:36.625 --> 12:38.166
Fine what?

12:38.250 --> 12:40.291
-It's more than that.
-I knew it!

12:40.375 --> 12:41.208
Since when?

12:41.833 --> 12:43.083
It's been a few months.

12:43.791 --> 12:45.458
You've hid it for months?

12:46.416 --> 12:49.125
-She doesn't want people to know.
-So are we just "people"?

12:49.208 --> 12:53.333
Bro, her followers must think
she's single. Attainable.

12:53.916 --> 12:56.875
-We're not her followers.
-You're still not?

12:56.958 --> 12:58.458
-No!
-We're your friends.

12:59.083 --> 13:02.625
So behave like friends.
Just give me some privacy.

13:02.708 --> 13:04.250
-Imaad, he wants privacy.
-Privacy.

13:04.375 --> 13:06.833
-We'll give him privacy.
-You piece of shit!

13:06.958 --> 13:08.958
You want privacy?
When are we gonna meet her?

13:10.000 --> 13:11.791
You want privacy, do you?

13:17.875 --> 13:19.000
Sorry.

13:21.041 --> 13:23.916
Seriously, bro,
this AI shit could end careers.

13:24.000 --> 13:26.208
Yours maybe. Mine hasn't started.

13:27.250 --> 13:29.666
It'll happen, man. You'll be fine.

13:30.166 --> 13:31.791
You're the man. You're good.

13:32.666 --> 13:34.041
Good doesn't cut it anymore, bro.

13:34.125 --> 13:37.500
These days you need to have your
own brand and celebrity clients.

13:37.583 --> 13:39.291
So? You have a celeb. Lala.

13:39.916 --> 13:43.208
Lala today, Lolo tomorrow,
then Bebo. Then Saifu!

13:48.666 --> 13:51.833
But seriously, man, I don't know
what the fuck I'm doing with my life.

13:54.000 --> 13:57.208
I want to open my own gym.
That'll be a game changer.

13:57.291 --> 13:58.250
So do it!

13:59.291 --> 14:01.125
You should've told me earlier.

14:01.208 --> 14:04.291
I have some rupees saved. I can open
two branches this week. What say?

14:06.375 --> 14:09.125
Man, I have no idea what I'm doing either.

14:09.208 --> 14:11.916
Tell you what.
Let's try till we're thirty.

14:12.000 --> 14:15.458
And if nothing works out,
Ahana will support us both.

14:15.541 --> 14:17.625
I'm sure she's already planning for it.

14:18.208 --> 14:19.958
Ahana's sorted, man.

14:21.250 --> 14:22.750
What is she doing with Rohan?

14:24.625 --> 14:25.833
Rohan wants a break.

14:26.416 --> 14:29.083
-What?
-I didn't say a word. You know nothing.

14:30.958 --> 14:32.833
Rohan wants a break from Ahana?

14:34.583 --> 14:36.458
-Guts.
-I know.

14:37.250 --> 14:38.208
Guts.

14:39.500 --> 14:40.833
-Bottoms up!
-Bottoms up!

15:02.666 --> 15:04.750
PLEASE CALL ME. I'M WAITING.

15:26.833 --> 15:29.375
Why has Rohan posted
a photo of a cake at dawn?

15:29.958 --> 15:30.958
What?

15:31.500 --> 15:33.708
-Bro, that's a cupcake.
-Same thing.

15:33.791 --> 15:35.416
How's it the same thing?

15:35.500 --> 15:37.750
-A cupcake is part of the cake family.
-So?

15:37.833 --> 15:40.000
A cupcake has its own identity.

15:40.083 --> 15:42.791
Its own personality.
You'd call a pastry a cake?

15:42.875 --> 15:44.333
-You nuts?
-A pastry is a pastry.

15:44.416 --> 15:45.375
-You're mad.
-You are.

15:45.458 --> 15:47.916
If I post a photo of an Alsatian,
I can't call it a dog?

15:48.041 --> 15:50.083
-South Bombay elitist!
-You call Messi by name.

15:50.166 --> 15:51.875
-Navi Mumbai isâ€¦
-Your dad's houseâ€¦

15:51.958 --> 15:53.750
Shut up! Just shut up!

16:02.916 --> 16:05.916
I want a break, or I want to break up?

16:06.958 --> 16:09.916
Ahana, is the Adrena-Fit
proposal deck ready?

16:10.000 --> 16:12.708
-I've mailed it to you.
-Great. Thank you.

16:13.583 --> 16:16.708
You planned the whole strategy
and she'll take the credit.

16:18.291 --> 16:20.583
He uploaded a photo of a cake
this morning.

16:20.666 --> 16:23.875
-What?
-Yeah, cupcake. And a heart.

16:23.958 --> 16:25.208
Cupcake?

16:27.166 --> 16:28.250
Let's check.

16:29.375 --> 16:35.125
Stacy Gomes, Mrinalini Jaisinghani,
Trisha Mariwala, Anoushka Gupta.

16:35.708 --> 16:37.333
-Kylie Jennerâ€¦
-Kylie Jenner.

16:37.416 --> 16:39.291
Dude, all boys follow Kylie.

16:39.375 --> 16:42.083
-Who's the dream girl?
-Ayush's sister.

16:42.166 --> 16:45.041
-Butter Cupcakes?
-Open that.

16:47.666 --> 16:49.750
This is where the cupcake was from.

16:52.333 --> 16:53.958
"Tanyabuttercupfly."

16:55.250 --> 16:56.125
Tanya Mehra.

16:56.208 --> 17:00.250
Just a girl with a sweet tooth
and a sweet life. Sparkle emoji.

17:01.458 --> 17:03.666
Always remember to sprinkle laughter,

17:03.750 --> 17:07.291
spontaneity and kindness
onto every single cupcake.

17:07.375 --> 17:10.041
#baketheworldabetterplace.

17:12.375 --> 17:13.458
Let me see.

17:20.583 --> 17:24.125
-Let's check her stories.
-She'll see my name.

17:24.625 --> 17:27.250
We'll make a fake account. Give.

17:31.000 --> 17:34.458
"I want a break" basically means,
"I want to hook up with someone else."

17:35.166 --> 17:38.458
You said you were never in a relationship.

17:38.541 --> 17:40.208
-Then how so sure?
-I know, right?

17:40.291 --> 17:41.875
Maybe I should be a therapist.

17:42.416 --> 17:45.125
But I can't pull off your cardigan look.

17:46.666 --> 17:49.500
You come to this session
to talk about you.

17:50.125 --> 17:52.333
Not about Ahana or my cardigan.

17:52.416 --> 17:53.750
Aren't we stuck in a loop?

17:54.333 --> 17:57.208
I think you've built a wall
around yourself.

17:58.500 --> 18:01.083
And you won't let anyone in.

18:02.541 --> 18:04.833
But you deserve a healthy,
loving relationship.

18:05.541 --> 18:09.000
What I really deserve is for dad
to stop sending me to these sessions.

18:11.583 --> 18:14.000
You know, Imaad, the thing about shame is

18:14.541 --> 18:18.875
the more you hide it, the more it grows.

18:20.291 --> 18:23.916
-But when we've talked about it--
-It's been 14 years.

18:25.166 --> 18:26.750
Let's both forget it.

18:31.083 --> 18:32.750
Where did you buy your cardigan?

18:34.125 --> 18:36.291
-You're sure this will work?
-Trust me, bro.

18:37.083 --> 18:39.958
It'll strengthen the glutes,
build endurance,

18:40.041 --> 18:42.583
-and it'll also protect the knees.
-That's good.

18:42.666 --> 18:44.916
That's it. Squat, hold that, stabilize.

18:45.000 --> 18:47.000
Pelvis tucked in. Chest up, bam!

18:47.083 --> 18:49.875
-Shoulders drop, yeah.
-Perfect.

18:49.958 --> 18:52.791
-Let's go for one last. Just on one leg.
-All right.

18:52.875 --> 18:54.708
This will strengthen your glutes.

18:55.250 --> 18:58.208
-It'll build endurance.
-One, two.

18:58.750 --> 18:59.666
One more.

18:59.750 --> 19:02.416
Protect the knees from injury.
Drop your shoulders.

19:02.500 --> 19:03.833
Lengthen the spine.

19:04.708 --> 19:06.500
Breathe. Smile.

19:09.625 --> 19:13.708
-Why can't I look like Malaika?
-Why do you need to?

19:13.791 --> 19:16.500
Take care of yourself
and that makes you beautiful, right?

19:17.125 --> 19:19.791
C'mon, nine, ten.

19:20.375 --> 19:21.625
C'mon, Anita, let's go.

19:22.958 --> 19:23.833
Eleven.

19:24.666 --> 19:26.750
I might not know Uganda's capital,

19:26.833 --> 19:30.166
but I know what Malaika Arora wore
to the gym yesterday.

19:31.708 --> 19:33.958
Even our attention span is
getting shorter.

19:34.041 --> 19:36.000
We used to watch five-day test matches.

19:36.083 --> 19:39.208
And now if a video isn't interesting
in the first five seconds,

19:39.291 --> 19:40.708
we go, "This guy is a drag!"

19:41.625 --> 19:44.833
I think the only people
who can perform in less than five seconds

19:44.958 --> 19:46.250
are Indian men in bed.

19:50.291 --> 19:51.791
Too close to home, ma'am!

19:53.250 --> 19:54.708
Are you guys together?

19:54.791 --> 19:55.750
Sorry, sir.

19:58.958 --> 20:02.333
We come across someone's profile
who has a life we aspire to have,

20:02.416 --> 20:04.625
we instantly follow them.

20:06.083 --> 20:09.166
We feel insecure and depressed
looking at the profile,

20:09.250 --> 20:10.958
but we are willingly following it.

20:11.041 --> 20:12.541
How stupid is that?

20:13.291 --> 20:16.291
If you want a daily reminder
that you're a disappointment,

20:16.458 --> 20:17.458
just call your dad.

20:17.541 --> 20:20.458
He's still wishing his son will
change the world one day.

20:22.083 --> 20:27.875
I read a survey that an average person
checks their phone 224 times a day. Wow!

20:27.958 --> 20:31.250
If you're repeating an activity
224 times a day,

20:31.333 --> 20:33.541
it's not an activity, it's an addiction.

20:35.541 --> 20:38.833
And we have become addicted
to other peoples' lives.

20:38.916 --> 20:42.708
Enough! We've got blinders on
and our brains in a straitjacket.

20:43.916 --> 20:46.833
I don't want to know what you're doing,
thinking or eating.

20:46.958 --> 20:48.250
